flipper and body mass in green

ggplot(data=penguins) +
   geom_point(mapping= aes(x= flipper_length_mm, y=body_mass_g),color="green")

writing to geom code in same dataviz

ggplot(data=penguins) +
  geom_smooth(mapping= aes(x= flipper_length_mm, y=body_mass_g)) +
  geom_point(mapping= aes(x=flipper_length_mm, y=body_mass_g))
## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'loess' and formula = 'y ~ x'
## Warning: Removed 2 rows containing non-finite values (`stat_smooth()`).
## Warning: Removed 2 rows containing missing values (`geom_point()`).

## writing different line geom for different species of penguins

ggplot(data=penguins) +
  geom_smooth(mapping= aes(x=flipper_length_mm, y=body_mass_g, linetype=species))
## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'loess' and formula = 'y ~ x'
## Warning: Removed 2 rows containing non-finite values (`stat_smooth()`).

jitter helps us deal with overplotting, jittering making

ggplot(data=penguins) +
  geom_smooth(mapping= aes(x= flipper_length_mm, y=body_mass_g)) +
  geom_jitter(mapping= aes(x=flipper_length_mm, y=body_mass_g))
## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'loess' and formula = 'y ~ x'
## Warning: Removed 2 rows containing non-finite values (`stat_smooth()`).
## Warning: Removed 2 rows containing missing values (`geom_point()`).

barchart

ggplot(data=diamonds) +
  geom_bar(mapping= aes(x=cut, color=cut,fill=cut))

## fill the clarity instead of cut ( which will show stacked barchart)

ggplot(data=diamonds) +
  geom_bar(mapping = aes(x=cut, fill=clarity))

Facet

Note : Using facet in given database

show the relationship between body mass and flipper in different penguins

ggplot(data=penguins, aes(x=flipper_length_mm, y=body_mass_g)) +
  geom_point(aes(color=species))+
  geom_smooth(mapping= aes(x= flipper_length_mm, y=body_mass_g))+
  facet_wrap(~species)
## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'loess' and formula = 'y ~ x'
## Warning: Removed 2 rows containing non-finite values (`stat_smooth()`).
## Warning: Removed 2 rows containing missing values (`geom_point()`).

creating the facet for creating each category of diamond cut

ggplot(data=diamonds) +
  geom_bar(mapping = aes(x=clarity, fill=cut))+
  facet_wrap(~cut)

removing sex

ggplot(data=penguins)+
  geom_point(mapping = aes(x=flipper_length_mm, y=body_mass_g, color=species)) +
  facet_grid(~species)
## Warning: Removed 2 rows containing missing values (`geom_point()`).
